name: lexicographicallyPrecedes(_:by:)
desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the sequence precedes another sequence in a lexicographical (dictionary) ordering, using the given predicate to compare elements.
declaration: func lexicographicallyPrecedes<OtherSequence>(_ other: OtherSequence, by areInIncreasingOrder: ((key: MLDataValue, value: MLDataValue), (key: MLDataValue, value: MLDataValue)) throws -> Bool) rethrows -> Bool where OtherSequence : Sequence, (key: MLDataValue, value: MLDataValue) == OtherSequence.Element
